import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', bins=30, kde=True, color='blue')
    median_speed = data['speed'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_speed, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_speed:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='dir', y='speed', hue='dirCat', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and direction?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction (degrees)')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.legend(title='Direction Category', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='dir', bins=36, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['dir'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['dir'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of wind direction?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Wind Direction (degrees)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='dirCat', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind direction categories?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Direction Category')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
